text: Josifović () is a Serbian surname, a patronymic derived from given name Josif (English equivalent Joseph). It may refer to: * (1868–1941), Serbian brigadier general of the Royal Yugoslav Army * (died 1941), guerrilla, member of Serbian Chetnik Organization *Stanislav Josifović, politician in the Serbian puppet Commissioner Government *Emilijan Josifović, Orthodox priest, signatory of Vukovar resolution ==See also== *Josipović, Croatian variant *Josifovski, Macedonian variant Category:Serbian-language surnames
title: Josifović
